# And the ones that can stack:
# We have a problem here: we may need multikey support.
# For an example, MAP01 contains three power cores.
# The first one is needed to exit from the Dream of Hell into Cold Rock caves.
# The second one is needed to activate the elevator and reach the barracks.
# The third is needed to open the door leading to the woods.
# (There are actually two more in a secret developer-only room, for a total of five.)
# So, logically, if you have zero, hell is in logic
# If you have one, hell and the caves are
# Two, hell, the caves, and the barracks
# Three+, the entire level (barring other item requirements)
# For an added complication, tokens are not map scoped.
# So, for example, having one power core means it could be used in MAP01 to fire
# the cannon and leave the dream, or in MAP04 for something else. Which means we
# need key logic for them. Argh. And we need to tell if the game has removed them
# from the player's inventory or something and reinstate them, but only if they
# weren't expended "properly"...argh.
# I think for now we just treat these as keys, and revisit the problem later.
# We may also want to split the "is this map- or cluster-scoped" bit into a
# new category, e.g. ap_map_scope and ap_cluster_scope; key implies it but we
# can set it manually on other things. This will also help for per-level weapon
# grants!
category key:
  InventoryBowlOfScribeEmbers
  InventoryCrimsonSaltRock
  InventoryCyanCrystal
  InventoryDarkIronOre
  InventoryDwarvenSuit
  InventoryIronBar
  InventoryIronLever
  InventoryIronOre
  InventoryMithrilOre
  InventoryMortarOfEarthPigment
  InventoryPowerCore
  InventoryPurpleRoot
  InventoryRedCrystal
  InventorySoulKeyFragment
  InventorySpiritGem
  ;

